><hr size=1> A while back I was on a Hole raid, planning to get my piece from High Scale Kirn for my Spear of Fate (SHM).  I was 46th level.  About 2-3 hours into the raid, as we got ready to climb the steps in Kirn's Tower (not KURN's tower .. but hmmm....) .. the sponsoring guild told me that I wouldn't get a chance on it (before I had joined the raid I had specifically asked if I would have a shot at it, and they had said yes) - because I 'wasn't high enough level to get my spear anyway' (well THANKS guys - /rude in RL).  Anyway, a short time later Lirus came back with my /petition and said, basically this:<br>
*<br>
You can't finish an epic quest and get a reward until you're 50+ level.<br>
*<br>
I was a *LITTLE* pissed off.  Up until that night, I had done all of my epic questing SOLO (with some unexpected help on the black dire, and I grouped with a necro to take down that damn paladin when he was an even fight).  I knew I wouldn't be able to finish it solo, but I'd put a LOT of work into my quest so far - I didn't have a guild that could/would really help me, and so I did it all myself.<br>
  I had a bit of a vent session with Lirus over this (and I'm STILL mad, but I understand GM's aren't responsible for content) - but my arguement, in sum, is this:<br>
If I'm powerful enough to KILL MY GOD then why can't I get my epic?<br>
(yes, you won't kill your god solo - but I can't finish my epic solo, either - shouldn't the cut off be 46th?)<br>
Lirus doesn't seem to think so.  He could be wrong.  He's only a GM.  &lt;snicker&gt;<br>
   - Paghk &amp; Dogdog, MT<br>
.... I've got a REALLY good rant on Alla's somewhere about this .... probably somewhere in the shammy epic pages, eh? <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showPrevMessage?topicID=3960.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showNextMessage?topicID=3960.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3960.topic&index=5><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/reply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.emailToFriend?topicID=3960.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.threadControl?topicID=3960.topic><img src=http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/dagger.jpg border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3960.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=3960.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion">Main Lounge<option value="thesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc">News Bulletin<option value="thesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies">Training Studio<option 